Project Description:
Phases 1 and 2 of the project delivered the baseline capability for RBTIS to support regulatory decision making in the residential aged care environment. Phase 3 commenced on 1 July 2021 with a focus on:
1) Finalising outstanding Phase 2 scope items;
2) Implementing Home Care Risk Profiling Phase 3 (designed to support the Commission to continuously add and refine their risk models for regulation of home care providers);
3) Continuing to expand on the acquisition of additional data including financial and prudential data;
4) Tailoring the existing Information Sharing platform for end users; and
5) Development of additional Prudential and Financial Risk Models.
